I want to start off this by saying that I LOVE taco bell. It has been a staple for my family since we were poor people growing up. You can easily sub beans in to make it vegetarian-friendly and honestly if your stomach can't handle the food then I feel bad for you sorry you're missing out. Now I don't come in here expecting a perfect order, especially in a location that also serves alcohol but I was pleasantly surprised when my entire order was doubled. Instead of 2 burritos, nachos, and a Mexican pizza, I received 4 burritos, 2 sets of nachos and 2 pizzas. I was truly as happy as can be. The staff are definetly overworked but I had always found them to be friendly and more than willing to fix any major errors they have made. I would also again like to point out that this location serves alcohol infused Baja blasts. My life is complete. Taco Bell as a whole is my go to night out spot, but this one is at the top of my list as an all-time favorite.

Cross your fingers that your visit here won't be during a busy time when the drunken Wicker Park crowd rushes in. Seats will be hard to find. The decor inside is pretty 'hip' with graffiti and some pretty cool looking lights, to match the vibe of the area.
